  ⚠️ MERGE STRATEGY — READ BEFORE CLICKING MERGE

  This repository enforces **atomic commit discipline** via four gates:
    - commit-msg        → commitlint (angular preset)
    - pre-commit        → git-absorb --dry-run (no-fixup gate)
    - post-commit       → atomicity classifier (writes .git/NON_ATOMIC_COMMIT)
    - pre-push          → pre-push-atomicity-gate (blocks non-atomic commits)

  The gates are preserved across merges ONLY if you use "Rebase and Merge".
  Squash-merge collapses all commits into one — **DO NOT USE IT**.
  Plain merge commits add noise; avoid unless explicitly required.

  If admin has run scripts/configure-merge-strategy.sh on the repo, only
  "Rebase and Merge" will be available in the GitHub UI.
-->

